Nigerians have reacted to the news of the lifting of the Twitter ban by President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday. Recall that the Federal Government approved the lifting of the suspension of Twitter operation in Nigeria effective from 12am tonight, 13th January 2022, after over six months of suspension. According to most Nigerians on social media, the reason for lifting of the suspension of the micro blogging app is due to the fast approaching 2023 general elections. Nigerians On Twitter Mourn Death Of Baba Suwe Twitter Ban: Activist Rinu, Tackles El-Rufai Over Using App… An Instagram user, psalmwrite wrote, “2023 election na your mate?” Another Instagram user, @asiwajulerry wrote, “Election is fast approaching, Awon Werey.” iambiggysteve wrote, “Election is coming soon. We know this scope.” declutter_territory commented, “Ahhhhh campaign don start.” cuathemoc wrote, “Election don near Dem need tools, watch influencers mode.”